&lt;p&gt;Thanks Marius! And thanks for all the comments/reviews.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15173296" author="mariusneo" created="Tue, 1 Mar 2016 06:18:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tflobbe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tflobbe&quot;&gt;tflobbe&lt;/a&gt; shouldn&apos;t this commit land also on origin/branch_5_5 ? I see it on origin/master now, which means that it will be available only on version 6.0 of solr. &lt;br/&gt;
Also the pull request &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/pull/14&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/pull/14&lt;/a&gt; is still open.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15174352" author="tomasflobbe" created="Tue, 1 Mar 2016 20:17:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was being lazy and not backporting. 6.0 will be out soon, and this Angular UI is not default in 5.x, so the impact is even smaller. &lt;br/&gt;
We don&apos;t need PRs for multiple branches, I can just cherrypick the commit from master to the branch if needed, would you mind close it yourself since I didn&apos;t mention it in the commit message?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
